  27,52,"These are their houses in utter ruin, for they did wrong. Verily, in this is indeed an Ayâh (a lesson or a sign) for people who know."
  27,53,"And We saved those who believed, and used to fear Allâh, and keep their duty to Him."
  27,54,"And (remember) Lût (Lot)! When he said to his people.{1} Do you commit Al-Fâhishah (evil, great sin, every kind of unlawful sexual intercourse, sodomy) while you see (one another doing evil without any screen)?",footnotes:1:{27:54} i.e. the town of Sodom in Palestine - the place where the Dead Sea is now. (See the book of history by Ibn Kathir ‘The Stories of the Prophets’). (كتاب التاريخ لابن كثير).
  28,25,"Then there came to him one of the two women, walking shyly. She said: "
  28,26,"And said one of them (the two women): "
  28,27,"He said: "